An array is as input and we have to make a new array that is an copy of input array by 2 times.

if input array is input 
then: 
     output  : input + input

Input: nums = [1,2,1]
Output: [1,2,1,1,2,1]


Logic: we take an new array that stores the values that is double the size of orginal array. We use the % operator to get the reminder.
       So : we iterate from i to 2n - 1 and keep adding elements in the input array to the output array  output[ i] = input [ i % n]


Code:
class Solution {
    public int[] getConcatenation(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;

        int[] ans = new int[ 2 * n];
        for( int i = 0; i < (2 * n); i++)
        {
            ans[i] = nums[ i % n];
        }

        return ans;
   
        
    }
}
